  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: \r\n\r\nTimestamp in Home screen shows time when a message was received but should show sent date instead:\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/42095237-53045176-7bb2-11e8-8af2-8e77987ff15d.png\" width=\"200\">\r\n\r\nThe message was sent 3:32PM. The chat shows it correctly:\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/42095281-72b3367c-7bb2-11e8-9fe5-9a4bd3852734.png\" width=\"200\">\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nTimestamp of a chat in Home screen shows time of the last message (either sent or received).\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nTimestamp shows time an incoming message was received. \r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status on 2 devices\r\n- Create 1-1 chat between devices\r\n- Kill the app on device 1\r\n- Device 2: send a message to device 1\r\n- Device 1: Open the app, login and wait to see the message in Home\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: 0.9.21\r\n* Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n",
